{"absolute_url":"https://boards.greenhouse.io/canonical/jobs/5295557","data_compliance":[{"type":"gdpr","requires_consent":false,"requires_processing_consent":false,"requires_retention_consent":false,"retention_period":null}],"education":"education_required","internal_job_id":1993595,"location":{"name":"Home based - EMEA"},"metadata":[{"id":186225,"name":"People management responsibilities?","value":false,"value_type":"yes_no"},{"id":149021,"name":"Employment Length","value":"Full-time","value_type":"single_select"},{"id":675557,"name":"Core skills","value":["Analysers","Competitor","Designer","Developer","Inventor","Organiser","Problem Solver","Scientist","Technologist","Tester"],"value_type":"multi_select"},{"id":2739136,"name":"External Departments (website)","value":["Web & Design"],"value_type":"multi_select"},{"id":2739137,"name":"One line job description","value":"Lead UX design for a pioneering web service as part of Canonical's enterprise and consumer open source offerings.","value_type":"long_text"},{"id":3209541,"name":"Canonical site","value":[],"value_type":"multi_select"},{"id":3587161,"name":"LinkedIn Posting Level","value":"Entry level","value_type":"single_select"},{"id":11961371,"name":"Featured job (Talent Team to complete)","value":true,"value_type":"yes_no"}],"id":5295557,"updated_at":"2023-11-08T02:45:26-05:00","requisition_id":"787","title":"UX Designer - Workplace Tools","pay_input_ranges":[],"content":"The role of a UX Designer - Workplace Tools at Canonical\nCanonical has been remote-first since 2004, and continues to raise the bar on employee collaboration and workplace experience design for this new way of working. You will lead the design of web applications for company processes, bringing exciting new projects to life and improving existing ones. We mainly want to build the perfect tooling for our own operation, but we may want to offer some of these capabilities as SAAS solutions to other crazy but brilliant companies, too.\nOur mission is to make enterprise-grade open source software, applications and services available to people everywhere. We create world-renowned software, impacting the lives of millions of engineers, enterprises, entrepreneurs and consumers every day. Our multi-disciplinary web design and production team includes visual designers, UX designers, front-end and back-end developers to bring exciting web projects to life. We help and learn from each other and strive to improve our work and processes.\nThis role sits in the design team reporting to one of the UX managers.\nLocation: This role will be based remotely in the EMEA region.\nWhat your day will look like\n\nPlan and conduct research with target users and stakeholders from across the business\nIdentify and document users' needs, business requirements and KPIs\nCreate new data-flows, dashboards and visualisations that automate and accelerate work \nDesign services and user experiences that improve employee's lives and get things done\nLead your projects, driving design and delivery against agreed goals\n\nAlmost 20 years ago, with Ubuntu, Canonical created the first Linux for human beings. Our design team is on a mission to turn complex, open-source software into intuitive products that can change the face of enterprise IT. We are looking for exceptional designers, who share our passion and want to bring Linux to millions of desktops.\nRead more about the design team\nWhat we are looking for in you\n\nExcellent academic results at school and university\nBachelor’s or equivalent in User Experience, Design, or STEM\nKnowledge and passion for user experience, technology and design\nCommitment to continuous learning and improvement - curious, flexible, scientific\nDrive to finish work and celebrate success\nConfidence in user research practices\nEngagement with the latest design research and innovation\n\nUX designers should be excellent communicators who are at ease working with a complex mix of engineers, designers and executives. They represent us at cross-functional company meetings and must present their design position with clarity and precision. They should be confident and excited to take on complex design challenges. They should also be able to connect their design leadership to the strategic vision of the company.\nWhat we offer\n\nAn opportunity to shape a company and products\nInfluence in the open source community\nAn inclusive work environment\nLearning and development\nAnnual compensation review\nRecognition rewards\nAnnual leave\nPriority Pass for travel\n\nCanonical is a growing international software company that works with the open-source community to deliver Ubuntu, the world’s best free software platform. Our services help businesses worldwide reduce costs, improve efficiency and enhance security with Ubuntu.\nWe are proud to foster a workplace free from discrimination. Diversity of experience, perspectives, and background create a better work environment and better products. Whatever your identity we will give your application fair consideration.\n#LI-Remote#LI-ET1","departments":[{"id":82569,"name":"Marketing","child_ids":[],"parent_id":null}],"offices":[{"id":44278,"name":"Home Based - EMEA","location":null,"child_ids":[],"parent_id":73277}],"compliance":null,"demographic_questions":null,"questions":[{"description":null,"label":"First Name","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"first_name","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Last Name","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"last_name","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Email","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"email","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Phone","required":false,"fields":[{"name":"phone","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Resume/CV","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"resume","type":"input_file","values":[]},{"name":"resume_text","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Describe your most complex web design project.","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_42078233","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Which new design patterns have you embraced, and which have you discarded, in the past year?","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_42078234","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Which companies do you think are innovating best in web design and design practices?","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_42078235","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Please attach a PDF portfolio if you have one available","required":false,"fields":[{"name":"question_42078236","type":"input_file","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"What time zone are you in?","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_42078237","type":"multi_value_single_select","values":[{"label":"Europe, Middle East or African Time Zones","value":151226985},{"label":"American Time Zones","value":151226986},{"label":"Asia Pacific Time Zones","value":151226987}]}]},{"description":"<p>Universities around the world score degrees in different ways. Please indicate your result, or expected result if you are close to graduation, along with information about the grading system.</p>","label":"What was your bachelor's university degree result, or expected result if you have not yet graduated? Please include the grading system to help us understand your result e.g. ‘85 out of 100’, ‘2:1 (Grading system: first class, 2:1, 2:2, third class)’ or ‘GPA score of 3.8/4.0 (predicted)’. We have hired outstanding individuals who did not attend or complete university. If this describes you, please continue with your application and enter ‘no degree’.","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_42078238","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"How did you perform in mathematics at high school?","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_42078239","type":"multi_value_single_select","values":